# Component Development Rules

## Required Skills

Before creating/modifying components, read:
- `plugins/portfolio-tools/skills/design-system/SKILL.md`
- `plugins/portfolio-tools/skills/component-scaffolder/SKILL.md`

## Patterns

- Use `'use client'` only when component needs interactivity (hooks, event handlers)
- Use BEM-style class naming: `component__element--modifier`
- Use refs for DOM access, not direct querySelector
- Use passive event listeners for scroll/mouse events
- Import constants from `@/lib/constants` instead of hardcoding values

## Structure Template

```tsx
'use client' // Only if needed

import { useRef, useEffect, useState } from 'react'
import { CONSTANT_NAME } from '@/lib/constants'

interface ComponentNameProps {
  // Define props with explicit types
}

export default function ComponentName({ prop }: ComponentNameProps) {
  const elementRef = useRef<HTMLElement>(null)
  
  useEffect(() => {
    const element = elementRef.current
    if (!element) return
    
    // Event listeners with passive option
    element.addEventListener('mousemove', handler, { passive: true })
    return () => element.removeEventListener('mousemove', handler)
  }, [])
  
  return (
    <section ref={elementRef} className="component-name">
      <div className="component-name__content">
        {/* Content */}
      </div>
    </section>
  )
}
```

## CSS Classes

This project uses a mix of:
- Custom CSS with BEM naming (in `styles/globals.css`)
- Tailwind utilities for quick styling
- CSS variables for colors: `var(--color-accent)`, `var(--color-0)`

## Reveal Animations

Use these classes for scroll-triggered reveals:
- `.reveal` - Base reveal class
- `.reveal-delay-1` - 0.1s delay
- `.reveal-delay-2` - 0.2s delay

## Image Handling

```tsx
import Image from 'next/image'

<Image
  src="/images/section/image.webp"
  alt="Descriptive alt text"
  width={800}
  height={600}
  className="component__image"
  priority={false} // true for above-fold images
/>
```
